            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Here are a few notable *very recent* AI items (as of March 4, 2026), spanning industry, policy, and research:\n\n- **Ethics / safety:** A **Brown University study** warns that people using chatbots like ChatGPT for therapy-style advice face risks because the systems can **routinely violate core therapeutic ethical standards**, even when instructed to behave like trained therapists.【6:1†source】\n\n- **Space robotics:** **NASA’s Perseverance rover** reportedly completed the **first AI-planned drive on Mars**, where AI planned routes using imagery/terrain data instead of the traditional human-only planning workflow.【6:1†source】\n\n- **Enterprise / products:** **Anthropic expanded “Claude” into enterprise workflows** via job-specific agents and integrations (e.g., Slack/DocuSign-style corporate tools), reflecting the ongoing shift from chatbots toward “AI coworkers” embedded in business processes.【6:0†source】\n\n- **AI research direction (long context):** Google Research published work on long-context approaches including an architecture called **Titans** and a framework called **MIRAS**, part of the broader push to make models handle more information reliably over long sessions/documents.【6:2†source】\n\nIf you tell me whether you care most about **consumer AI**, **business/enterprise**, **policy/regulation**, or **research breakthroughs**, I can narrow this to the most relevant “latest” stories for you.",
